parameters:
Would you like to view the event? Early Departure from a
Black Company

\nc<Senpai>Saki, you're being dispatched to the media today, don't
forget.
\nc<Senpai>Then make me the beneficiary of your life insurance, please.
\bustMsgExp[2, 1]\nc<Senpai>Do you hate being dispatched to the media that much?

\nc<Saki>Do you know what the other succubi have been saying about me
since that ridiculous interview was broadcasted?
\nc<Saki>They're calling me "the disgrace of the succubi"...

\bustMsgExp[2, 0]\nc<Senpai>Well... that must have been tough. Is that all you wanted to
say?
\nc<Saki>Tch... Fine. I'll go if I must, I'll go.
\nc<Saki>(Only considered an ace at times like this...)
\bustMsgExp[2, 1]\nc<Senpai>Huh? Oh... I see. Don't worry about it.
\bustMsgExp[2, 0]\nc<Senpai>Good news, Saki. Today's dispatch has been canceled.
\bustMsgExp[1, 4]\nc<Saki>Really? Have my prayers finally reached the heavens...?

\bustMsgExp[2, 1]\nc<Senpai>If you really had such power, I'd ask you to kill our
executives too.
\bustMsgExp[2, 0]\nc<Senpai>Ahem! Anyway, you can leave early today.
\bustMsgExp[1, 1]\nc<Saki>Huh? What, what, whatttt!? An early departure!?

\nc<Senpai>Do you not want to? You've seemed tired lately, so I thought
I'd be considerate... If you don't like it, you can stay and
work overtime with me...

\bustMsgExp[1, 0]\nc<Saki>I'll be leaving first! I'm going to take full advantage of
the freedom I've been given and set out on a journey!
\nc<Senpai>Wait, sign this contract before you leave.
\nc<Saki>A contract...? Do I need a contract to leave early?

\nc<Senpai>Yes. It states that you'll take responsibility for anything
that happens while you're away. And there are a few strange
clauses that you don't need to know about.

\nc<Senpai>This is normal for us. Sign quickly and go home. Almost no
one has actually been penalized because of this.

\nc<Saki>So not zero then. But for an early
departure...\bustMsgExp[1, 0]there!
\nc<Senpai>Good work. Now go and rest up.
\nc<Saki>(Phew, that ended more easily than expected)

\bustMsgExp[2, 1]\nc<Senpai>Oh, and just to be clear... if you go out and it affects
your attendance tomorrow, I won't let it slide, okay? If
work comes up, I'll call you back in, so stay put at home
quietly.

\bustMsgExp[1, 2]\nc<Saki>I don't have the energy for that...\bustMsgExp[1, 3]Well
then, thank you for your hard work!

\nc<Employee>Eh, an early departure from our team... Senpai... what are
you scheming this time?
\bustMsgExp[2, 0]\nc<Senpai>You'll understand whether you like it or not in a few days.
